{"title_page": "1941 North Dakota Agricultural Bison football team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college football season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n  |year=1941\n  |team=North Dakota Agricultural Bison\n  |sport=football\n  |image=\n  |image_size= \n  |conference= North Central Conference\n  |short_conf=NCC\n  |record=2\u20137\n  |conf_record=2\u20134\n  |head_coach= [[Stan Kostka]]\n  |hc_year=1st\n  |stadium=[[Dacotah Field]]\n}}\n{{1941 North Central Conference football standings}}\nThe '''1941 North Dakota Agricultural Bison football team''' was an [[American football]] team that represented North Dakota Agricultural College (now known as [[North Dakota State University]]) in the [[North Central Conference]] (NCC) during the [[1941 college football season]].  In its first season under head coach [[Stan Kostka]], the team compiled a 2\u20137 record (2\u20134 against NCC opponents) and finished fourth in the NCC.<ref name=NDAMG>{{cite web|title=2013 Bison Football Media Guide|publisher=North Dakota State University|page=156|url=https://s3.amazonaws.com/sidearm.sites/gobison.sidearmsports.com/documents/2013/9/13/NDSUFBGuide2013Pg151-160.pdf|accessdate=April 24, 2019}}</ref> The team played its home games at [[Dacotah Field]] in [[Fargo, North Dakota]].\n\nPrior to the 1941 season, the Bison had not won a game against a NCC opponent since 1938. The team broke the streak with two conference victories in 1941.<ref name=NDAMG/>\n\n==Schedule==\n{{CFB schedule\n| attend = y\n| source = y\n\n|September 19||{{cfb link|year=1941|team=Concordia Cobbers|title=Concordia (MN)}}|[[Dacotah Field]]|[[Fargo, North Dakota|Fargo, ND]]|L 7-13||<ref>{{cite news|title=Concordia Upsets Bison Eleven, 13-7|newspaper=Minneapolis Morning Tribune|date=September 20, 1941|page=9|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36192632/concordia_upsets_bison_eleven_137/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|September 27||{{cfb link|year=1941|team=Morningside Maroons|title=Morningside}}|Dacotah Field|Fargo, ND|L 6-25||<ref>{{cite news|title=Maroons Defeat Jacks, 25 to 6|newspaper=Waterloo Sunday Courier|date=September 28, 1941|page=35|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36192604/maroons_defeat_jacks_25_to_6/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|October 4|at|[[1941 Montana Grizzlies football team|Montana]]|[[Dornblaser Field]]|[[Missoula, Montana]]|L 0-27|> 3,000|<ref>{{cite news|title=Sparkling Plays Score Four Montana Touchdowns|newspaper=The Sunday Missoulian|date=October 5, 1941|page=6|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36079979/sparkling_plays_score_four_montana/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|October 11||[[1941 South Dakota State Jackrabbits football team|South Dakota State]]<hc>|Dacotah Field|Fargo, ND|W 25-0||<ref>{{cite news|title=Bison Nab 25-0 Win Over State: North Dakotans Get First Conference Grid Victory Since 1938|newspaper=The Daily Argus-Leader|date=October 12, 1941|page=9|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36192345/bison_nab_250_win_over_state/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|October 18||{{cfb link|year=1941|team=Omaha Indians|title=Omaha}}|Dacotah Field|Fargo, ND|W 13-6||<ref>{{cite news|title=Bison Defeat Omaha, 13-6|newspaper=The Sunday Argus-Leader|date=October 19, 1941|page=8|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36192586/bison_defeat_omaha_136/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|October 25|at|[[1941 North Dakota Fighting Sioux football team|North Dakota]]|[[Memorial Stadium (University of North Dakota)|Memorial Stadium]]|[[Grand Forks, North Dakota|Grand Forks, ND]] ([[Nickel Trophy|rivalry]])|L 6-20||<ref>{{cite news|title=Sioux Whip Bison, 20-6: North Dakota University Whips State Rivals in Conference Game|newspaper=The Sunday Argus-Leader|date=October 26, 1941|page=8|url=https://www.newspapers.com/clip/36192283/sioux_whip_bison_206/|via=[[Newspapers.com]]}}</ref>\n\n|November 1|at|[[1941 Iowa State Teachers Panthers football team|Iowa State Teachers]]|[[O. R. Latham Stadium]]|[[Cedar Falls, IA]]|L 6-51|1,500|<ref>{{cite ne